ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: We learned how to design, interpret, and analyze impact evaluations. It was a mix of quantitative and qualitative work. I would recommend this class to anyone who plans to work in development.
Recommend if you're interested in a phd or other career in development research
Yes, the class was good and I learned a lot
Great content, you will learn a lot. Be ready to put in some work of your own and make a effort to approach the Professor

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This is the single most useful class I took during my year at Yale. I expect to refer back to this material many times in the future, and to keep a copy of Mostly Harmless Econometrics with me at future jobs.
Great understanding of research methodology and how to apply to development studies
